Only minor differences in clinically inactive components are allowable in biosimilar products.

elements.text: Biologic drugs are expensive and the widespread use along with rising demand for these products is huge financial burden for the healthcare system. Biosimilar medicines increase access to patients who can benefit from biologic medicines but cannot afford the costs. In addition biosimilars could lead to earlier intervention with the appropriate biologic medicines, potentially improving treatment outcomes. What is more, by facilitating more affordable options, biosimilar medicines can allow healthcare providers freedom to reallocate resources towards other areas of patient care.
